	<text>
		<body>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_hirschberg_rutka">Rutka Hirschberg</persName> Testimony (doc. 301/1129)</p>

			<p>Original, manuscript, 2 pages, 210 x 295 mm, Polish language</p>

			<p><pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011129_01.jpg"/>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_hirschberg_rutka">Rutka Hirschberg</persName>, 14 years old.</p>

			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-206" type="subject">Aryan papers</term>.</p>

			<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/709611/drohobych.html">Drohobycz</placeName>.</p>

			<p>Record taken by <persName ref="#ehri_et_bauminger_roza">Bauminger</persName>.</p>

			<p>In <date when="1939">1939</date> we left <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Wilno</placeName> and headed for
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/702550/lviv.html">Lvov</placeName>. My parents wanted to take me to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/709611/drohobych.html">Drohobycz</placeName> and then to return to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/702550/lviv.html">Lvov</placeName>. When we reached <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/709611/drohobych.html">Drohobycz</placeName>, my parents found work there and we all stayed there. I
				went to school right away. I kept my best memories from this school. On <date when="1941-06-22">June 22, 1941</date> the Russo-German
					<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080">war</term> broke out. The day before I had
				received my school certificate, I had been on a school excursion, and nobody had been thinking about the <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080">war</term>. In the morning terrible noises woke us up. We thought
				these were just military drills but then the radio and newspapers put us right. The evacuation of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/709611/drohobych.html">Drohobycz</placeName> began. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">army</term> left. The situation was unclear. The
				worst was when the Bolsheviks left the town and the <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> still
				weren’t there. <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_ukrainians">Ukrainians</term> went mad then. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-346" type="subject">Pogroms</term> began. <term type="subject"
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_ukrainians">Ukrainians</term> would go from house to house with truncheons, axes, stanchions, and
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-345" type="subject">beat Jews</term>. One man wanted to save us but
				his <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">wife</term> did not let him save the Jews. We
				didn’t even hear the <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> enter. Their first <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-338">orders</term>. Jews are allowed to buy things on the market square
				only within <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-337" type="subject">specified hours</term>. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-338" type="subject">Armbands</term> were introduced, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-579" type="subject">Judenrat</term> was organized. They robbed a great
				deal, and gave away for the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-488" type="subject">contingents</term> the
				poorest ones who couldn’t ransom themselves.</p>
			<p>One particular situation remained etched in my memory. Nearby, there was a very rich <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans"
					type="subject">German</term> delicatessen. The owner’s daughter, very pretty, the picture of health, slapped a Jewish <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824">child</term> on the face, dressed in rags, who had
				asked for a piece of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">bread.</term></p>
			<p>From time to time, Job’s news of the coming action. We would go into <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262"
					type="subject">hiding</term>. In the wall of the attic there was a hole through which we crawled into our <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">hideout</term>. It was so low <pb n="2"
					facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011129_02.jpg"/> we had to lie flat on the floor.</p>
			<p>We got work in the roofing-tile <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929">factory</term>,
					<orgName ref="#ehri_et_stadtische_ceramische_werke">Städtische Ceramische Werke</orgName>,<note type="gloss">Städtische Ceramische
					Werke – Municipal Ceramic Factory</note> near the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669"
					type="subject">prison</term> of Brygidki.<note type="gloss">Brygidki – prison in Lwów</note> It was a sealed <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> for <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">girls</term>, they lived in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barracks</term> behind the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929" type="subject">factory</term>. The roof of the <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837">barracks</term> was leaking. They worked hard thinking it would save
				them from <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-115" type="subject">deportation</term>. At first it was
				possible to go out into town from there with a pass. During the actions in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/709611/drohobych.html">Drohobycz</placeName> there was a terrible panic in the roofing-tile <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929">factory</term> as well. We <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hid</term> in a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">summer-house</term> near the <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929">factory</term>. The <term type="subject"
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> didn’t think that somebody might have <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hidden</term> in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">summer-house</term> which was just by the <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929">factory</term> gate and that’s how we managed to avoid
					<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745">death</term>. They put all the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">girls</term> onto the trucks then. As one of the <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929">factory</term>’s managers, Daddy defended them, then
				one <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS man</term> took out a pistol and wanted to
				shoot Daddy. At this moment one <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Polish</term>
				<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">woman</term>, looking at all this from the upper
				floor, gave a terrible scream. This must have disconcerted the <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term>
				for he hid the pistol. Very many <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">girls</term> were
				taken that time to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-41" type="camp">Bełżec</placeName>.</p>
			<p><foreign xml:lang="de">Städtische Werkstätte</foreign>. The most talented youth <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">worked</term> there, coming from the most influential
					<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819">families</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/709611/drohobych.html">Drohobycz</placeName>. They made beautiful things: sculptures and paintings
				showing folk life, toys. It seemed to be the safest <foreign xml:lang="pl">placówka</foreign> [workplace]. Once (it was after I left,
				I know this from what my friend told me) an automobile with <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216"
					type="subject">SS men</term> arrived and the whole youth was loaded onto the automobiles. They behaved like heroes. With heads
				held high they sang <q>Poland is not yet lost</q>, <note type="gloss">“Poland is not yet lost” – the Polish national anthem.</note>
				<q>Hatikvah</q>, <note type="gloss">Hatikvah – Zionist song, currently the national anthem of Israel.</note>
				<q>La Marseillaise</q>
				<note place="bottom">La Marseillaise – the French national anthem.</note> and <q>The Internationale</q>
				<note type="gloss">The Internationale – a communist song, former national anthem of Soviet Union.</note> and that’s how they drove
				through the town knowing that they were going to their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745"
					type="subject">deaths.</term></p>
			<p>In <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/709611/drohobych.html">Drohobycz</placeName> there was also a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term>
				<q>Beskidy</q>. I don’t know much about it, apart from that the richest people gathered there. It lasted the longest. When they
				realized that they were being hounded they hid in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject"
					>hideouts.</term></p>
		</body>
